    <p>Timeless Timing Attacks</p>
  </div>
  <div class="page">
    <p>Timeless Timing Attacks  Absolute response timing is unreliable, as it will always include</p>
    <p>jitter for every request</p>
    <p>Lets get rid of the notion of time (hence timeless)</p>
    <p>Instead of relying on sequential timing measurements, we introduce concurrency and only consider response order =&gt; no absolute timing measurements</p>
    <p>Timeless timing attacks are unaffected by network jitter</p>
  </div>
